        "title": "Add Agents tab New Agent flow",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a Control UI Agents tab New Agent action and dialog for name, workspace, model, emoji, and avatar.\n- Submit through the existing `agents.create` Gateway RPC, refresh `agents.list`, verify the created agent is returned, and select it.\n- Reuse the existing provider-qualified model option contract so catalog entries like `{ id: \"gpt-5.5\", provider: \"openai\" }` persist `openai/gpt-5.5`.\n- Force and sequence the post-create list refresh so stale in-flight `agents.list` responses cannot make a successful create look failed or reset selection.\n- Block creation while unsaved config edits are pending, add focused controller/view coverage, refresh i18n fallback entries, and update the changelog.\n\nFixes #81947.\n\n## Issue Triage\n\n- #81947 was not already resolved on current `main`: the Agents tab had refresh/select/edit handlers but no create action, while the Gateway/SDK `agents.create` contract already existed.\n- No open tied PR was found. The closest prior implementation was #35790, but it is closed and unmerged.\n- #13346 is the stale duplicate report for the missing Create Agent button; PRtags search/annotation/group APIs returned 502, so I applied the repo's live GitHub duplicate labels (`duplicate`, `dedupe:child`) to that already-closed issue instead.\n\n## Review Fixes\n\n- Addressed ClawSweeper's model finding by extracting a shared catalog model-option helper that qualifies model ids with providers before rendering/submitting create-dialog values.\n- Addressed ClawSweeper's refresh-race finding by adding an agent-list request generation and using a forced refresh after create; older list responses are ignored if a newer forced reload starts.\n\n## Bug/Security Review\n\n- The UI sends only schema-supported `agents.create` fields: `name`, `workspace`, optional `model`, `emoji`, and `avatar`.\n- The Gateway remains the authority for workspace path resolution, duplicate/reserved-id rejection, identity sanitization, config persistence, and workspace/transcript creation.\n- The new rendering uses Lit bindings and existing translated strings; no `innerHTML`, `unsafeHTML`, eval, storage, cookie, or navigation surface was added.\n- The submit path blocks when the config form has pending edits so creation does not race with unsaved Agents config changes.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/agents.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents.test.ts --run` (2 files, 27 tests)\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/agents.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents-utils.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/agents.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents.test.ts`\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `git diff --check HEAD~1..HEAD`\n- `pnpm ui:build`\n\nRemote changed-gate attempts before the review-fix commit:\n\n- `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider blacksmith-testbox --blacksmith-org openclaw --blacksmith-workflow .github/workflows/ci-check-testbox.yml --blacksmith-job check --blacksmith-ref main --idle-timeout 90m --ttl 240m --timing-json --shell -- \"env CI=1 NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=4096 OPENCLAW_TEST_PROJECTS_PARALLEL=6 OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 OPENCLAW_VITEST_NO_OUTPUT_TIMEOUT_MS=900000 pnpm check:changed\"` allocated `tbx_01krmbfpsx142ed931bzpna1bt`, but it remained queued and was stopped.\n- `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider aws ... pnpm check:changed` failed because AWS credentials could not be refreshed on this machine.\n- `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider hetzner ... pnpm check:changed` failed because `HCLOUD_TOKEN` / `HETZNER_TOKEN` is not configured.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\nBehavior addressed: The Control UI Agents tab now has a New Agent flow that calls `agents.create`, refreshes the agent list with stale-response protection, verifies the created agent appears, and selects it.\nReal environment tested: Local macOS Codex worktree with focused Agents controller/view tests, targeted oxlint, Control UI i18n validation, whitespace validation, and production Control UI bundle build.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/agents.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents.test.ts --run`; `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/agents.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents-utils.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/agents.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents.test.ts`; `pnpm ui:i18n:check`; `git diff --check`; `git diff --check HEAD~1..HEAD`; `pnpm ui:build`.\nEvidence after fix: 2 test files passed with 27 tests; targeted oxlint reported 0 warnings and 0 errors; i18n check reported all 18 locales clean; diff whitespace checks passed; Vite built the Control UI bundle successfully.\nObserved result after fix: The create controller rejects duplicates before RPC, sends valid create payloads, forces a stale-safe `agents.list` reload, selects the created agent, and the Agents view renders provider-qualified model options plus duplicate validation and disabled duplicate submit state.\nWhat was not tested: Full `pnpm check:changed` in Testbox/Crabbox was blocked by external capacity/credential setup; live browser/Gateway manual agent creation was not exercised.\n",
